{
  "texts": [
    "More recently, there have been demonstrations of quantum error correction using real-time control in various systems 2,6,71,72.",
    "There have also been examples of work toward classical-control microarchitectures that enable the seamless integration of qubits and classical operations with tens of qubits.Our work was performed with the first-generation real-time control system of IBM Quantum, in which we use centralized processing of mid-circuit measurement outcomes to classically condition a quantum circuit.",
    "The control system architecture is based on a hierarchical heterogeneous system of field-programmable gate array controllers with computing elements for concurrent real-time processing, microwave control and qubit readout.",
    "These are synchronized through a global clock and linked with a real-time communication network to enable synchronized collective operations such as control flow.",
    "Branching incurs a constant latency penalty to execute the branch (of the order of 500 ns)."
  ]
}